<item>
            <title>[LU-17280] LFSCK inconsistent OI fixed line spamming</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17280</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;LFSCK directory scanning founds the dir that contains a shards. Shard name is a FID, so LFSCK has FID to inode mapping from a directory entry. LFSCK put this FID/inode mapping to inconsistent list, to check this mapping using OI and scrub. And it produces msg inconsistent OI fixed.&lt;/p&gt;
